  "_comment": [
    "noise[t]  = NEW CVEs disclosed in the module that quarter (the canary). Source:",
    "  api.osv.dev /v1/query, deduped by alias cluster (GHSA<->GO<->CVE = one advisory),",
    "  earliest `published` date sets the quarter. A property of the PACKAGE.",
    "signal[t] = of those, how many are REACHABLE on Console7's call path (the toil owed).",
    "  Source: govulncheck v1.1.4 (built with go1.25.11) `-json ./...` at t0=2026-06-25.",
    "  RESULT: 0 reachable across the whole build. 13 advisories are present at",
    "  module-required level (golang.org/x/crypto v0.51.0, ssh/* fixed in v0.52.0) but",
    "  UNREACHED (ssh packages not imported) => signal 0. Console7 is govulncheck-clean by",
    "  reach, exactly as the go.mod header claims. This is the measured t0, not an assumption.",
    "Window: 2024-Q1..2026-Q2 (contiguous quarters). Advisories predating the window:",
    "  grpc +1 (2023-Q4 HTTP/2 Rapid Reset), protobuf +1 (2023-Q1), x/crypto +9 (2021-2023).",
    "signal=0 for every period: pre-adoption (Console7 took these deps at 2026-Q2 t0) there",
    "  was no call path; at t0 govulncheck measures 0 reachable. Both are honestly 0 -- the",
    "  series is Console7's TRUE starting record, and will accrue real signal>0 only if a",
    "  future reachable CVE lands. Quiet (noise=0) modules carry one t0 anchor; their verdict",
    "  is cross-checked against `health` (Scorecard/libyear) per the model -- noise=0 alone is",
    "  ambiguous (could mean nobody is looking).",
    "health{}: OpenSSF Scorecard (api.deps.dev) + libyear drift (proxy.golang.org version",
    "  dates). mirror=true marks modules developed on Gerrit (go.googlesource.com) whose",
    "  GitHub mirror Scorecard under-reads -- detected via the ?go-get=1 VCS host, so it",
    "  catches x/* AND google.golang.org/protobuf; treated LOW-CONFIDENCE, never inflates H.",
    "advisories{}: per-module advisory detail (CVE/GO id, published, fix version) so each",
    "  noise count is traceable to the specific CVEs behind it (e.g. grpc CVE-2026-33186",
    "  fixed 1.79.3, below our v1.80.0 pin -> unreached)."
